<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued July 28 at 7:12PM CDT until July 28 at 8:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 815 PM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN OLDHAM AND WESTERN HARTLEY COUNTIES...
At 711 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Romero, or 15
miles northeast of Nara Visa, moving north at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Romero.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.
Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
